    • Method Detail

      • getName

        public java.lang.String getName()
        Returns the name of the figure. The name of the figure will always match the HashMap key for this figure. The figures in the problem will be named A, B, and C for 2x1 and 2x2 problems. The figures in the problem will be named A, B, C, D, E, F, G, and H in 3x3 problems. The first row is A, B, and C; the second row is D, E, and F; and the third row is G and H. Answer options will always be named 1 through 6. The numbers for the answer options will be randomly generated on each run of the problem. The correct answer will remain the same, but its number will change.
        Returns:
        the name of this figure
